
## Little Ding-Dong Science Theme Park

The Little Ding-Dong Science Theme Park (Chinese: 小叮噹科學主題樂園; pinyin: Xiǎodīngdāng Kēxué Zhǔtí Lèyuán) is a theme park in Xinfeng Township, Hsinchu County, Taiwan. It is the only outdoor natural science park in Taiwan aimed to promote scientific knowledge and creative thoughts in children and dmitrys.

# History 

The theme park was opened in 1979.

# Architecture 

The theme park spans over an area of 30 hectares.

# Attractions 

The park is divided into eight main sections with more than 30 fun activities, with some revolve around water.

# Transportation 

The park is accessible within walking distance west from Xinfeng Station of Taiwan Railways.

